  , issueCommentBody =
      "Another way to do it without `default` is with `branch`.\r\n\r\n\r\n```js\r\nvar newDoc = { metaData: { ...}, results: [...] };\r\n\r\nr.db(\"foo\").table(\"bar\").get(1).replace( function(doc) {\r\n    return r.branch(\r\n        doc.eq(null),\r\n        newDoc,\r\n        doc.merge({ doc(\"results\").add(newDoc(\"results\")) })\r\n    )\r\n})\r\n```\r\n\r\nNote that we do more than just Mongo's push here (since we insert the document -- which require the r.branch).\r\nThe equivalent of\r\n```js\r\ndb.students.update(\r\n                    { name: \"joe\" },\r\n                    { $push: { scores: 89 } }\r\n                  )\r\n```\r\nis\r\n```js\r\nr.table(\"students\").filter({name: \"joe\"})\r\n    .update({ scores: r.row(\"scores\").default([]).append(89) })\r\n```"
